data.text:
Westwind Brass

Westwind Brass (WWB) is a professional brass ensemble devoted to increasing peopleâ€™s awareness of music. The Los Angeles Times and others have acclaimed WWB for its virtuosity, musical integrity, and diverse programming.

Performing since 1986, WWB has received recognition as a top prizewinner in two international brass competitions. WWB has performed for the Music Educators National conference and has given frequent performances for the California Music Educators Association state conferences.

Our public concerts offer a kaleidoscopic set of styles and composers from the rich Baroque sonorities of Handel and Bach to the music of world cultures. Serious art music including the jazz of Dizzy Gillespie and Thelonious Monk are embraced.

In residence at San Diego State University, the ensemble is nationally recognized for its critically acclaimed residencies, educational performances and concerts.

WWB is internationally recognized for its critically acclaimed residencies, educational performances and concerts. Featured in their residency programs is non-Western music from Africa, China, the middle east, and South America. The ensemble has performed for the Music Educators National Conference, the first Chamber Music Educator/Ensemble Seminar at Oberlin, and has spent many weeks in residency in Japan, Mexico, and through all regions of the United States.
